description.narrative: (Zimbabwe): The Strengthening Private Sector Support for Health (SPSS) mechanism aims to reduce morbidity and mortality by increasing coverage of national malaria prevention and treatment interventions. With FY 2014 funds, SPSS will:-Distribute 880,000 Long-Lasting Insecticide Treated Nets (LLINs) in targeted areas. Increasing the coverage of LINNs will reduce malaria incidence and decrease related morbidity and mortality-Conduct a pilot distribution of LLINs within antenatal care (ANC) services in two districts in order to make the distribution of nets a routine part of ANC services.-Support a malaria training needs assessment and provide training and follow-up support to 1,200 primary health care workers on malaria case management. This training will reduce malaria case fatality by improving early access and treatment of malaria cases. -Support malaria behavior change communication activities to increase uptake of all malaria interventions.-Support training of health workers in monitoring and evaluation of malaria interventions.
